Pleon.Epimeral plates (Fig. 22
E-G
): plate I ventrally rounded, bearing three setae and one spine on anteroventral margin and four setae on posterior margin; plate II with one seta and two spines on ventral margin and six setae on posterior margin, posterodistal corner blunt; plate III with two spines on ventral margin and five setae on posterior margin, posterodistal corner subacute.

Oostegite (Fig. 25
E-G
): oostegite of gnathopod II broad, oostegites of pereopods III and IV elongated, oostegite of pereopod V smallest.
